Short Python `.gitignore` covering bytecode, environments, tooling, builds, PyCharm, macOS.

```gitignore
# Byte-compiled / cache
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class

# C extensions
*.so

# Virtual environments
.env
.venv
venv/
env/
ENV/
.python-version

# Package/build artifacts
build/
dist/
wheelhouse/
*.egg-info/
*.egg
.eggs/
pip-wheel-metadata/
pip-log.txt

# Installer logs
pip-log.txt
pip-delete-this-directory.txt

# Unit test / coverage
.coverage
.coverage.*
htmlcov/
.pytest_cache/
.tox/
.nox/
.cache/
coverage.xml
*.cover
*.py,cover

# Type check / analysis
.mypy_cache/
.dmypy.json
.pyre/
.pytype/
ruff_cache/
.pyright/

# Jupyter
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# Logs
logs/
*.log

# Django / Flask specifics (optional; remove if unused)
*.sqlite3
instance/
db.sqlite3

# Local settings
local_settings.py

# IDE / Editor
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp

# macOS
.DS_Store

# OS / misc
Thumbs.db

# Generated docs
docs/_build/
site/

# Lock / dependency managers (optional keep if you commit them)
Pipfile.lock
poetry.lock

# Cache of tools
.pyre/
.bandit

# Temporary
tmp/
temp/

# Ignore secrets pattern (adjust as needed)
*.env
*.secret
secrets/
```